::DarkMouse::

She got up and put her rat in it's cage.  She walked over to her room 
and looked around.  She quietly shut the door behind her.  She leaned 
against the door and looked at her room.  She remembered why she ran 
in the first place and wanted to cange into a maximal.  It was 
because she found out how cold the predacon spark really was.  She 
couldn't stay here and feel apart of the predacon team.  She was 
predacon now.  She felt her spark tearing in two.  She held down her 
emotions and swallowed her pride.  They had just retrieved her and 
would be watching her.  She would bide her time and wait until the 
time was right. But that time wasn't now. Later. It would be later.
